text: Ramsey County is a county in the U.S. state of Minnesota. As of the 2020 census, 552,352 people lived there, making it the second-most populous county in Minnesota. The county seat is Saint Paul, which is also Minnesota's state capital. The county was founded in 1849 and is named for Alexander Ramsey (W), the first governor of the Minnesota Territory. == References == Category:1849 establishments in Minnesota Territory Category:Minnesota counties
title: Ramsey County, Minnesota
